schools, Dallas has some outstanding programs

25:49.375 --> 26:00.229
going on there. There are school districts and 
rural schools all over the state that have some

26:00.665 --> 26:07.355
exciting things going on. We want to use those as 
lighthouses and share the best practices that are

26:07.535 --> 26:14.044
going on. And the universities can help with that. 
We started a principal center in which we brought

26:17.790 --> 26:24.259
together a congress of principals, outstanding 
principals from all over the state. We had 58 of

26:25.184 --> 26:30.009
them here last summer in what we call the 
Principal's Academy. So we took House Bill 72 and

26:30.109 --> 26:39.960
said, how are we doing in implementing the 
Declaration of Independence? Where are the

26:39.980 --> 26:42.423
problems now? You know, performance appraisal 
was one. How do we do good performance appraisal?

26:46.888 --> 26:48.089
We actually set up some practices when we did that. 
We brought in resource people to help with this.

26:49.791 --> 26:51.613
The career ladder, we looked at that. We brought in 
people who were the principals of the schools that

26:51.863 --> 27:03.057
Sarah Lightfoot wrote about in her study of high 
school. The study showed some of the outstanding

27:03.077 --> 27:08.323
high schools in the country who brought the 
principals of some of those schools in. We need to

27:08.343 --> 27:09.285
do more of that. We need to share with each other 
what's the best ways to improve the quality of

27:09.305 --> 27:16.133
education. in the schools. Principals Academy, 
we can do, we set up nine clusters now around the

27:19.368 --> 27:24.276
state. We're also tied in with other universities 
in those regions to help with those principals, 58

27:24.336 --> 27:33.149
principals who attend the academy. Those 
principals will come back in November for a

27:33.169 --> 27:40.399
follow-up meeting and come back next summer for 
another full week in the academy. So we'll begin to

27:40.419 --> 27:44.365
have a network of practicing professionals who 
can, in fact, be a part of a network for

27:45.577 --> 27:53.549
implementing good practices. And they're all 
connected now with a hotline where we share

27:53.569 --> 28:01.741
information daily across these groups. So 
there's a lot of good things going on in Texas.

28:05.187 --> 28:09.573
There's a lot of interest on the part of the 
technology people who work with the state.

28:09.593 --> 28:12.638
They're just setting up interactive TV programs. 
They even pipe programs into schools with a small

28:14.703 --> 28:23.396
roast because we only had a small group of students 
at an advanced level studying certain kinds of

28:14.703 --> 28:23.396
things. You can connect several different 
schools. You can make up a class. And you can do this

28:27.863 --> 28:28.804
over interactive TV. Or if they don't have a 
chemistry professor or a biology professor, you

28:28.824 --> 28:37.337
can pipe this in through interactive television. 
Most programs are now in operation in Texas.

28:40.962 --> 28:43.005
They're not extensively developed yet, But 
they're on our way with us. And I think we ought to

28:46.078 --> 29:12.317
highlight the good things that are going on, 
because as a result of a lot of the dialogue that

28:46.078 --> 29:12.317
took place with this black committee, the morale 
of the teachers, especially, got very low,

28:46.078 --> 29:12.317
because they interpreted the being in the focus, 
they interpreted it as criticism, especially

28:46.078 --> 29:12.317
when the Nation at Risk came out and said, you know, 
our schools are in a shambles, and that we were

28:46.078 --> 29:12.317
going to, declare war or somebody was going to come 
in and try to defeat us, and they create schools

29:13.192 --> 29:21.981
like we've got now. We're committing unilateral 
disarmament by the way we set up our education

29:22.001 --> 29:27.327
system. Well, teachers can only take so much of 
that. And really, even the good teachers feel like

29:29.469 --> 29:33.053
they're being beat on. So if we can stop beating on 
the teachers and start emphasizing working

29:33.333 --> 29:41.882
together and helping at each of these levels, I 
think that effort-wise, we're doing as much or

29:42.453 --> 29:53.390
more than almost any other state.

29:53.470 --> 29:59.300
How does Texas rank with other states regarding 
public education? Well, you see, I think you can't

29:59.320 --> 30:06.691
answer that question unless you take a specific 
area. And the worst thing to do is to take SAT tests

30:09.824 --> 30:20.578
and do comparisons like the federal government 
did, because as I mentioned before, you know, only

30:09.824 --> 30:20.578
3% of the kids in North Dakota even take the test. 
32% in Texas take it. So comparing that data

30:22.401 --> 30:25.044
doesn't give you anything. You know, what you 
really need to do is take an area, like with career

30:26.266 --> 30:36.220
ladders, there are nine states in the country that 
are experimenting with career ladders. We're one

30:36.240 --> 30:37.661
of them. Now, whether that makes us better than the 
other 41 states, they're not doing anything on

30:40.385 --> 30:45.192
that yet. I don't know. It all depends on whether 
Clean Water ends up being better than what existed

30:46.013 --> 30:51.240
before. And we're in a state of piloting that, 
trying that. I think it will be better. I think it's

30:56.307 --> 31:02.916
better just because we're examining new ways to 
create a profession. Trying ways to keep good

31:03.605 --> 31:09.831
teachers in the classrooms without having to 
become administrators in order to make a decent

31:03.605 --> 31:09.831
salary. That's a good goal. Now whether we can do it 
or not is yet to be seen. But I'm proud to be in a state

31:15.537 --> 31:20.662
where we're trying.

31:20.682 --> 31:24.446
Are very many other states reforming public 
education? Quite a few of them. Quite a few of them.

31:27.669 --> 31:29.231
And they're doing it in different ways. I don't 
know too many of them. Perhaps New York and

31:31.012 --> 31:32.734
Tennessee. uh moving in in florida and maybe north 
dakota i'm moving in in a very comprehensive way

31:33.862 --> 31:59.717
probably texas and there's a more 
all-encompassing set of reforms than any place

31:33.862 --> 31:59.717
else that i know of i mean what we're trying to do is 
deal with all the whole thing the curriculum the

31:33.862 --> 31:59.717
way schools are staffed the way they're evaluated 
the way they're administered we're trying to do

32:00.018 --> 32:27.240
you know the way teachers are prepared the way 
they're evaluated we're

32:00.018 --> 32:27.240
dealing with everything in this reform package

32:00.018 --> 32:27.240
uh i can't think of any other state that has a more 
comprehensive

32:00.018 --> 32:27.240
reform package than texas it may be one of our 
problems you know because we're trying to do all of

32:00.018 --> 32:27.240
them at once And we're trying to do it in a short 
period of time. It's going to take some real

32:32.346 --> 32:49.841
sensitivity now to get, especially the teaching 
profession itself, involved in having some sense

32:32.346 --> 32:49.841
of ownership in this package, in implementing 
this package. All of the surveys we've done so far

32:49.861 --> 32:57.868
indicate that the teachers are supportive of a lot 
of these reforms, like career ladders. It's just

32:58.878 --> 33:09.571
that they have a lot of questions about the way 
they're being implemented and their lack of

32:58.878 --> 33:09.571
involvement in the design of them and the carrying 
out of them. After this fact, did we get them to feel

33:09.731 --> 33:18.221
some investment in this whole thing and change 
those things? We shouldn't be afraid to change

33:18.241 --> 33:25.510
those things that need changing because of the 
fact that it was such an all-encompassing bill It

33:26.063 --> 33:35.715
would be very natural now to go back and have to fine 
tune it without destroying the major elements

33:26.063 --> 33:35.715
of it. Do you have any personal ideas on other 
possible reforms for Texas that you would like to

33:35.735 --> 33:43.144
see implemented? Well, I'd like to see a system 
where we have much more opportunity

33:43.164 --> 33:53.978
for school districts to innovate and try 
different approaches to the way schools are

33:43.164 --> 33:53.978
organized I'd like to see a system where you have 
minimal options within the public education

33:54.717 --> 34:10.360
system, where you might have a school which is 
pretty much independently oriented, where your

33:54.717 --> 34:10.360
students do a lot of individual study and use a lot 
of technology. You might have some schools

34:10.381 --> 34:14.767
organized around more than once a SORI approach. 
You might have schools, some of them, run by

34:14.787 --> 34:19.935
industry in collaboration with the schools. You 
have a lot more work in terms of outside of the

34:22.477 --> 34:36.533
school activity and not have so much uniformity 
that doesn't allow a certain amount of uniformity

34:22.477 --> 34:36.533
in terms of goals and standards, I think you mean. 
But the way those goals and standards are

34:37.234 --> 34:44.502
implemented, that we should have a lot of 
opportunity and flexibility and autonomy. to

34:45.275 --> 34:49.119
meet those goals and standards. I think the role of 
the state ought to be to set those goals and

34:49.219 --> 35:05.836
standards, but allow maximum freedom for the 
local communities in collaboration with

34:49.219 --> 35:05.836
community resources of a variety of kinds to find 
different ways of implementing these standards.

35:05.856 --> 35:13.223
And I think that there are a lot of ways to use people 
in communities and resources that we haven't

35:05.856 --> 35:13.223
tapped yet. I think that the

35:13.979 --> 35:30.694
way we conceive of education, we ought to be 
thinking of it more in terms of from birth

35:13.979 --> 35:30.694
throughout all of life. People of all ages need 
education, and I can see us providing

35:30.834 --> 35:41.944
opportunities where you have some community 
education settings, where you have senior

35:30.834 --> 35:41.944
citizens, preschool children, children who are 
elementary and secondary, in the same

35:42.380 --> 36:03.802
environments where you have the senior citizens 
leaving for the four-year-old and using schools

35:42.380 --> 36:03.802
as learning resource centers for anybody

35:42.380 --> 36:03.802
and open up the way we can see them in learning 
environments.

